<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7206> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7206" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Tr. pl. 87 or 86. Sea Schol. Bern. on Lucan 2.125 (Usener), Marius Caelium tribunum  plebi sillanum de Tarpeio saxo praecipitavit. His identity remains uncertain, but he may be the tribune .whom  the younger Marius, according to Dio 30-35, fr. 102, 12, threw from the Capitol at the time of the New Year sacrifice in 86. If the Marius in question was Gratidianus, date and occasion for the death of Caelius become less certain. See below, on Marius (42). I wish to thank Elizabeth Rawson for drawing these passages on Caelius and Marius Gratidianus to my attention.\n" .
